            . I am a constable of Shadwell, and live next door to Mr. Moss. On the night of the 17th of July I went to my door, and saw the prisoner standing near his window - I crossed the way, and when I turned round he was gone; I thought he had stolen something - I followed,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182809110144"></xptr>and saw him with a pair of trousers in his coat; I took hold of him, and he dropped them.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded distress.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 39.</p>
